caption: I remodeled the bathroom in the basement and was given Shrimp and Grits and let me tell you thats one hell of an amazing dish.  The staff are all nice and cordial.  Service seems very prompt.  Live music and dj are here as well.  Get a nice vibe off this place.

The food was really good I ate my food,my mother’s and my little brothers . I had the funnel cake chicken biscuits. My little brother had the chicken and waffles and my mother got the deviled eggs , cheesesteak egg rolls and the jerk lamb chops  . I don’t like deviled eggs but those were really good.The funnel cake chicken biscuits was good . I kept eating my little brother waffle it was so delicious.

Service was slow and unorganized.  The hostess escorted me and my party to our table with menus but no utensils. Alcoholic drinks were watered-down and, I asked for glasses of water when the waitress first  came to the table. Water was brought out 1 30 mins after our drinks.  My party all ordered our food at the same time,.my meal arrived first, 20 mins later the other meals arrived but we not prepared correctly. I had to request eating utensils,.my cousin ordered steak and of course,  there was not a steak knife to cut it with.  Very disappointed with the quality of service!!!!!  Lamb chops  and asparagus were seasoned well, the rice pilaf was dry dry!!!

The last couple of times I've been there is always something floating my water. So order no ice! And pay the $5 for bottle water. Atmosphere and music is great. Server and drinks were ok. I will be back but how much longer... It would be nice if they addressed the ice situation, service food faster and stocked the bar ready for business. I'm sure it's until we get over this hump. Looking forward to coming back.
Great food and service. Beautiful venue.

Walk in lady at the front inform us it’ll be a 30-40 minute wait we agreed she took our number down. We waited in the car for an hour no call back for someone to call. We called back to inform them that we’ve been waiting for 2 hours and that no one has called back. No apologies the lady over the phone couldn’t find our number and then they found the phone number and said they were at capacity. She asked how many we inform her 2  ppl then ask could we come now if so how long?...NEVER AGAIN 👎 NO APOLOGIES A WAISTE OF TIME... very unprofessional

My wife and myself went to the civil resturant Saturday evening the food was great my wife had salmon with rice I had lamb chops and mac n cheese on the other hand the service was not great our server Em made our experience really good the kitchen cannot keep up with the volume of orders they are receiving hopefully the next time we go to the civil its better

Great food and drinks but the service was really bad it’s disheartening because this spot has the potential to be great but it’s missing the X factor when it comes to restaurant service. I will only order carryout from the spot from now on. It’s not one I will visit again via dine in. Hopefully you all can improve on your service in the near future for other diners.

This spot I’ve heard about many times but I never had the chance to get here. Went on a friday night around 9:45pm.Immediately the music selection was good, every song a good song , R&B, new soul and slow jams. There was a wait about 20-25 minutes. Many people were entering and exiting but the wait to be seated was a while. I want to say we sat down around 10:20ish. Before that the live band started playing and singing. We got seated and a waitress came over introduced herself and took out orders. The menu has a lot of option and they portions are big. I ordered the jerk soft tacos and honey Brussel sprouts. They were out of the Brussel sprouts she  suggested the cauliflower bites - honey lemon pepper with buffalo sauce on the side. The  tacos were great, a lot of meat and a good portion. The bites came out hot and crispy. I ordered the Pink champagne which was thee best and 1 tequila shot. Overall the the customer  service was good. the waitress kept coming to check on us,  the atmosphere was a vibe and the open mic when different people started singing was a vibe. I would definitely return to this place but I would arrive a little earlier.

This place is alright, the ambience is cool but the lighting was terrible. I don't understand why they had bright lights. It wasn't intimate at all. I felt like I was in a diner or a school cafeteria. Dj was cool.  The bathroom is downstairs which is weird to me. Some people might not be able to use the stairs smh. I ordered crabby fries and was also going to order the chicken and waffles, but when I saw the crabby fries I changed my mind. My cousin ordered hot wings, they were really good. However my crabby fries were phoney, it was crab dip plastered on top of some fries. I was expecting the ooey-gooeeyness of melted cheese and lump crab meat on the fries, not crab dip. If you like crab dip then you might like these. It looks like tuna salad. My palette was a little upset lol, so I didn't finish it. My cousin and her friend ate them.  The service was kinda slow it looked like there were only 3 waitresses. Our waitress was cool.  I would return to try something different and hopefully the service is faster.  It is black  owned.

I’m going to be honest, this is black owned so I really did have high expectations but this was one of the worst experiences I’ve had during the entire pandemic. First off, the atmosphere was lively however I waited over 2 hours for appetizers and my entree. Both were cold and did not taste good at all. After waiting hours for my food and it being nasty and cold I asked for a refund the manager said I could not get one after knowing my food took hours. She offered to make something else, which took another 45 mins. I got there 8:30. I left around 11 (closing) bc the service was so long. I spend $125 all together and I only consumed 2 drinks and a little bit of my appetizer. Total waste of money, they are extremely busy and need better chefs. I would not have minded waiting if the food was good but everything was cold and had no flavor. I would not come back or recommend anyone to come here.
That place is a trash can I will not eat there never again

The customer service  was great and welcoming. The food was very good. I would suggest only one appetizer because you get a good portion of food with your meal. Everything was very clean from the ladies room to the dining area. The drinks are not watered down. The price paid was reasonable!
Black Owned establishment that should be on the Map for excellence: excellent service, food, and drinks. Will be back!!!
The food is delicious and the staff is so nice make you feel at home
The food was delicious (with the exception of the hickory collard greens. They were way too sweet). The service was extremely slow. Maybe they were having an off day🤷🏾‍♀️.
The waiter was good. The food was not that great. The bathrooms were nasty.

Amazing!!! Everything tasted so delicious! My fiance and I came here for brunch! It was all you can eat! We also had their endless mimosa’s!!! Great experience! Excellent Excellent customer service!!! Can’t wait to return!!!
Service sucks, the manager (tall large female) sucks, just overall horrible experience both times that I have been here!!!
Great food, drinks, and atmosphere.

They only had 2 servers at Sunday Brunch and no hostess. We waited for about 15 minutes before even being greeted and then when we were finally asked to sign, we were asked 3 times by a waiter how many people were in our party. Only to be seated at a dirty table. The wait staff also seems like they don’t have real restaurant or hospitality experience. There was no real dimension to the “cocktails” we were served either. Almost like they just threw some stuff in a cup and put it on the table to drink.  Skip this place and go to somewhere more organized and equipped to handle their patrons with more ease and know how.  A for Effort F for Execution and Preparedness
Food and drinks are good. The prices are reasonable.  Usually ppl are 30 under.
Great food, great vibes! Live music was phenomenal! Food was so good that I wish I had more, yum!
The atmosphere was fantastic but my French toast wasn't all everybody was friendly so I'll definitely be back
The food was amazing...Servers are so nice and respectful..And the Live band was really cool...Will be back!!!
Nice atmosphere experienced only during 4p-7p, but that time there was GREAT! Whatever the Chef did to those Brussels Sprouts was magnificent♥️  My new go to place, thank you!
Great atmosphere, love the food and vibe
Great food and great vibes
This place was not all that I expected
Good food, Questionable service.
Went there for an interview. The venue is definently nice. Black Owned Business.

Went here for my daughter’s birthday on a Sunday. Waited two hours and 10 minutes for food. They didn’t have clean glasses for water. They ran out of food and the waitress knew it and never informed us. We left and went to Cheesecake Factory in Towson. Totally different experience. Don’t waist your time
The civil  is awesome, did my bday and my hubby  bday there, had a ball food good,drinks good and our waitress was the best ever..
The steak was so rough it should've come with laces fam!
Awesome service (shout out to Trey), food is outstanding. Clean and beautiful seating area.  No complaints.
Just went there for an interview, looks really 👍 Great
Black-owned.  Cool, chill vibe.  Soulful and occasional live music.  Good food, good drinks. Been here for Sunday brunch and Friday happy hour.  I liked both. I'll definitely be back.

Service was a little slow even though it wasn't busy. Drinks were overpriced, especially compared to the food/meal costs. Food was average, looks better than it taste. The side of spinach was extremely salty and had too much pepper, basically inedible. Disappointed, really wanted to support a black owned business.
The appetizers were delicious. The Jimbo buffalo shrimp and beef tacos were great! Our waitress was professional and a great attitude and gave wonderful service. 👍😊

Nice atmosphere chicken was good but I asked for a steak well done and it was delivered cold and blood red. Sides were also cold. They had one person delivering food and making drinks. And no attempt to correct the fact was I was served a living cow and cold mac and cheese. Would not recommend!
The food was good but they were out of a lot things and the bartender was slow
Definitely a bonus for the city
Great establishment, wonderful people ... very welcoming. Cant wait til everything opens back up that's deflee my new spot!!!!💕💯

The civil tacos are amazing I indulged yesterday for cinco de mayo and anyone who knows me knows I live for a good taco and a strong drink and with that being said the civil has u covered on both ends food and drinks are delicious  I will be back soon.
Amazing customer service and specials. The wings are amazing and the bartender is cute lol
Great place , and atmosphere can’t wait til this is over so we can get back to brunches and live music.
The attention to detail was amazing! The bartender got us right. It’s nice to see that through a pandemic people still practice kindness. The wings are the best!!!! Def check this spot out
Food is amazing, service is great, drinks are top notch! They never disappoint!

I eat here more times than I care to disclose, lol, but I love this place.  Their peach Hennessy is AMAZING!  I actually ordered food from here for my birthday, since COVID closed everything down, and I’ve been faithful ever since. My family loves it, and it’s my go to, whenever I’m hungry! Love this place!  My favorite time to come is Thursday, pre-COVID, because of the live performances. The performers are awesome, and the vibe is great. Definitely recommend this place.
The Civil has the best customer service i have every encountered. They have the best turkey club and wings. The drinks will definitely get you lit!!!
I love this place, it’s soooooo Beautiful!!! It’s for sure a vibe....
Great safe place with a chill and sexy atmosphere. Good food, a quality drink selection and the staff is friendly.  The patrons are just that.... CIVIL. Check it out

Beautiful black owned spot with a nice vibe. It's spacious with good drinks and music. I went on a Saturday night from 9-11pm. I had the strawberry champagne. It was delicious. I also had the 3 piece wings with mac n cheese as my side. The Hennessy bbq flavor wasn't the best, but the chicken was tasty and fried perfectly. The mac N cheese was a little on the watery side and needed more flavor. My friend loved his lamb chops and my other friend didn't like the jerk chicken tacos. The service from our waitress was superb, BUT the service time took forever. It took a while for our food and drinks to come out. I plan on going back. Gratuity is added to every bill. They do brunch as well.
Nice atmosphere but  a little pricey for the quality of food
One of the coolest spots in Baltimore definitely a must visit, the open mic performers were really good as well as the food and atmosphere.
Loved the civil! Especially on Friday nights. Get there early though, they may run out of everything you like..

Like others have mentioned, the atmosphere is nice, and the music is good. The compliments stop there. Nothing really sets this establishment apart from any other lounge in Baltimore. I thought operations and presentation  were more on the unprofessional side. There are definitely improvements that need to be made. Also, the service, drinks, and food are terrible, and overpriced! Also, keep in mind that gratuity is always added to purchases- tips are requested but optional. (Of course I tipped, but I always feel like a tip on top of gratuity basically means you’re paying the employees what the employer won’t).

What a cute place! Nice atmosphere-- perfect place to go for brunch or before a night out with the girls. Good music, seating and architecture. I wish that they'd plate the food for their late night menu instead of using trays and wax paper, but the food was great. Wonderful customer service.... I will be back.
Great happy hour! They were very accommodating to our large group! The entertainment was excellent. It was open mic night.
This was my first time visiting the Civil, The service was great and it's a cool, laid-back atmosphere. (I was there for my sis's birthday party)
Ajah/Asia was amazing! Food took a little while but worth the wait.  Thanks!

My wife and I chanced upon Civil following Lunar New Year celebrations at the Walters '. I believe this to be the building where I used to attend Louis ' Book Store many years ago and I think the glass doors are the ones from that earlier establishment. The fore part of Civil is somewhat gloomy and needs more lighting but we ate at the rear of the dining room and near the well lit bar. Civil is decorated in nouvoux something and reminiscent of the late 1930', with dark, padded two person dining tables: there's a posh wall covering of trompe d'oel effect faking padded and buttoned silk material. We passed up the buffet. My wife ordered a turkey club sandwich with 'fries and I opted for the Cajun Fettuccine Alfredo. The food arrived after a suitable period for cooking and it was fresh and hot. The server was adequately prepared to handle about ten folks who were dining at the time. My fettuccine was richly sauced , the pasta perfectly cooked, the peppers delicately sliced and the smoked sausage went down well with the Cajun named dish. The serving size was gargantuan, and I foolishly attempted to eat the whole serving instead of dividing out a take home portion: I swallowed a month's worth of cholesterol as a result. Our coffees were strong, piping hot and a far cry from the tepid offerings currently in vogue with our litigiously threatened catering industry. A good meal. This place may not have dessert spoons - or else they were all in the dish washing machine. There are several puddings on the menu and I do like to dive into a pudding wielding a dessert spoon, rather than the oversized teaspoons that seem common nowadays We exchanged a few words with a neighboring couple who praised their choices from the buffet meal and noting its freshness and adequate temperatures. It was their first time at Civil and they indicated they would be back. I will place Civil as the lunch place to visit each time we make our weekend trips to the Walters '. This will be a
This food is fantastic. All I can say is WOW

Any where that Black Owned is always a plus. Food is absolutely amazing and it’s a very reasonable price . My Favorite is the salmon with rice and a side of sautéed spinach , a must have 😋 and the lamb chops are also good . I enjoy my time there every time I go very good customer service live band and always different activities to do everyday .

Awesome Brunch spot! The mimosas and the brunch buffet was very tasty. The space is beautiful and I would love to plan a private party or something there. The service was excellent! They kept the Mimosas flowing non stop...and the love DJs were the icing on the cake

My twin sister and I had our 40th birthday private dinner event at The Civil ,January 2020. I would highly recommend this establishment for your high end private dinner party needs. All 50 of my guest raved about the mac n cheese, wings, fried rice,  meatballs, and string beans. The ambience is exactly what I wanted. My vision came to life at The CIVIL. Shay was beyond patient with me during the planning. Support this minority owned business. You'll be glad that you did.
It is a nice place. The food was good. The layout allows you most of the main floor. Some of the bartenders were attentive. The best part was the live music.  I hope to return soon.
The food and drinks are  great
Love this place
My old bay wings were good but my friends salmon was over cooked!! I enjoyed the music and the service was good.
Food was excellent. Went there for a Birthday brunch so I was able to taste breakfast and dinner items.

WARNING: I’m a huge critic. Nice place! Beautiful ambiance, I guess people can come really casual or really dressed up, although I did feel overdressed wearing heels while some guests had sweats on. I liked the food although it did take kinda long on a random Thursday evening, my friend ordered an appetizer as her main course (crab balls) and her order took the longest; it came by the time everyone else finished their entrees. The entrees were so incredibly small for the price though I was actually really surprised i paid close to 40 dollars for a cut of salmon (with a side salad that never came, but I don’t like salad anyway hehe) and crab mac and cheese sparse in crab and served in an appetizer style cup. Peach sangria was delicious. Definitely a spot to go to if you’re looking for a bar, and might like a snack later.  UPDATE: I went out with a friend for a date, he wanted to surprise me with a “new” place he’d heard of, aka the Civil. Once I saw where we were I gave him the run down of what I thought of this place. Nonetheless, we went in to basically a club scene, very loud live DJ, a huge crowd, people just standing, people sitting at tables that clearly had not been serviced. We understood the crowd because it was fight night, so we went upstairs and were greeted by women twerking all over the place lol... There was one waitress in the area, the food on the menu had definitely been updated and there were way more options than my first visit. About an hour went by and I waved the waitress down to ask if she would be okay with taking our order. She nicely told us that we had to order at the bar and they would bring our food up. It took my date about 20 minutes to get us drinks from the bar... We couldn’t even imagine how long it would take for us to order and RECEIVE our food. We left with nothing in our bellies. Also MANAGEMENT: please make sure guests are not sitting their drinks on the stairs! Huge safety hazard. Either be more strict or put out more tables.
The staff was good drinks were good but waaaaay overpriced! Ask for the price of the drink before ordering! The atmosphere was chill but food service was slow over all a good vibe live music was cool

This was the worse experience in my entire life. 1. The heat was not on in December 2. Twelve people in the restaurant and took almost an hour for appetizers 3. Staff was not friendly or inviting 4.Drinks too 45 mins to come 5. One person as host, waiter, and bartender 6. Food took an hour and was luke warm when it arrived. 7. The crabs balls were terrible, hard and dried out. Had to be reheated before. I would zero stars if I could. The manager came over and made an excuse that this was all due to a change in shifts. I will never return to establishment. Needs to shut down. They need chick fil a training. Horrible Horrible Horrible
The food was good, service was bad!
I really like this place my first time here the atmosphere is great and the staff are very accommodating thank you

Nice atmosphere, & can use some improvement! Took a while for us to receive out food and we received the appetizers the same we received the entrees! They didn't have any soft drinks the water tasted like tap water! The food wasn't so bad but the proportion size was a lil small. The waitress was cool. I think if they have regular drink options, get the get food out in a timely matter, and add more to the menu I'll go back

While the place is beautiful,  as stated in other reviews it took forever to get our food and it came out wrong, and the ran out of  spindip. After getting my food I had to ask for napkins and utensils.  The gave me drink napkins. My order was wrong and I did get my spindip. So I dont know if I would go again.
Great live music! What an open Mic night! The bar is huge but place seemed understaffed for its capacity. Staff was awesome and crabby fries...yummmm
NICE UPSCALE LOCATION ; DRINKS VERY EXPENSIVE

This place has a lot of potential. It looks nice and the music was great. The drinks were also good.  Everything else was horrible. It took hours to bring out food for myself and my guests. The waitress never gave us utensils (we had to go to the bar). When my food finally did come out it came with none of the sides. I waited another 45 minutes for that. It took an hour to grab our boxes and check. Then there were also discrepancies with the drink prices.  The menu said one price and we were charged another. This place is not worth it. The only thing that saved it was the music.  I don't think I'll go back.
Black-owned.  Very nice, cozy feel.  Live music occasionally.  Food was ok.  Ordered lemon pepper wings, and it tastes as if the lemon pepper, cajun and old bay wings all get tossed in the same bowl.

Worst experience I ever had in my life , it was maybe a good 20 ppl in the restaurant the night I went , not packed at all , it took our food over 2 hrs to come out , oh I forgot most of the items on the menu wasn’t available , when the food came out it was over cooked , very cold and greasy everything was taste less , the waitress was very nice , when the manger finally came over after we requested her , she was very unpleasant her attitude was horrible she was only willing to take off a couple dollars worst black business to date I will never return ,
Great place

Beautiful atmosphere.  Bartender was  not  very welcoming although she mixes a great drink. Food was subpar and not the least bit exciting. Its black owned with great music. Packaging is wonderful. Hopefully the cook will become more creative and thoughtful with his dishes.  I understand this is a fairly new establishment. I'm rooting for you all!

Really enjoyed myself tonight, the atmosphere and energy was amazing. I ordered Peach Hennessy which was good, and shortly after received my food, (Cheese steak Egg-rolls ) by employee suggestion. The staff was sufficient and friendly..... definitely will return, Thank you ❤️

My Husband and I went for lunch on a casual Friday afternoon and the service was amazing. Our waitress name was Lola and she took the time to help us with the menu gave us suggestions on what to order. We will definitely patronize this establishment again. Thank you from the Mitchell's
Nice place.. .need better food options.  Don't get the Rice yuck
Was a very nice place they were had open mic night when I went.
Great service good food and drinks

The place has a lot of potential. It needs more professionalism, from the doorman to the management. They pick and choose who enters the restaurant. Your friends can be denied entry at the doorman's discretion, even if they traveled  from far places. I wouldn't want that kind of situation again. Visit at your own risk.
The food was as sooo good, great service, fast service, Atmosphere was perfect I can’t think of 1 bad thing to say 😬...Barbecue chicken Dip Was The best I EVER Had‼️
Great Atmosphere, Great Food , Looks Amazing very pleased .........

The atmosphere was really nice. The drinks were really good but the food took too long to come and I was not impressed. It was ro salty and the kitchen kept forgetting one thing or the other. The menu needs revamping as well

Food was good but after spending $150 food and drink at the bar, they would not let us sit at the tables on the level with the ban. They saved those seats for others and put us in empty balcony. Only stayed because it was a friends birthday.
Slow service, is really good yet nice!!!!
Location, interior decor and atmosphere are all great at this bar & lounge. Potentially, thee spot for the black professional after work rendezvous. Very metropolitan...

Great poets and spoken word artist especially ntycement and sir Alex I would have given 5 stars but they have a bar area that is not enclosed and if that area is crowded, it can be hard to hear the artists.
probably the worst Alfredo I’ve ever had.... idk how u mess up Alfredo but they did!

The food order took an extremely long time and came out cold. The Alfredo was very bland, requested twice for old bay to help the flavors merge however they never brought it to us. I had really high hopes for this place and regrettably I was let down due to the quality of food and service.

My girlfriend and I went here for breakfast after wondering around Baltimore. It was us two and one other couple in the Entire restaurant. My girlfriend ordered  biscuits and sausage gravy while I ordered a Belgian waffle and eggs. The food took over 45 minutes to be served and when it finally was we were drastically disappointed. Her biscuit was very under cooked and was basically dough. My Belgian Waffle was paper thin and tasted very plain. (Not how a real Belgian waffle should be)  The waitress noticed my girlfriends plate was still full when we asked for the check and asked what was wrong, but there was no offer to re make or discount the meal. When we got the check we noticed that our juices were $4.00 a Peice and they added a mandatory 15% gratitude bringing our bill to $36!  Now I normally tip without an issue and would have done so because the waitress was very friendly. But I was shocked to see the price of their drinks and the quality of their food was definitely under par.
OMG this place gorgeous, the sever was amazing! You know it is good when the owner comes to great himself and take your dishes. Also the food was sooo good!
Great place. I had the peach Hennessy which was very good and also tried the honey lemon pepper tenders and they were delicious! Everyone should Try this place out! I’ll be back for sure 😉😌

This was a huge disappointment. The food came out incredible slow and in pieces. So people got their food at various times. The Belgian waffles are not in fact Belgian waffles, the bacon was plated without any intention or class. The waiter was great but my biggest complaint would be with the kitchen. Completely disorganized. Be prompt. This place has a lot to improve upon. The customer bathrooms are down stairs (inconvenient) but they have a staff bathroom in a very convenient space. Who does that? Will seriously think twice before coming here again.
Not too much of a beer or liquor selection but nice feel!
Really nice environment food was Amazing Great Place to have an event.
Such a lovely atmosphere! The food is good and the drinks are great.

Went for brunch and was disappointed. The server needs a lot more training--the number of times she said "not a problem" or "I'll make it work" when we asked for things like coffee and maple syrup (which never came) was shocking. A server really shouldn't use those phrases. She also came to double check what we ordered 3 different times over 25 minutes. Our food should have come out by the third time she stopped by. When our food did arrive, it was underwhelming. The waffle is like a thin Eggo, omelette didn't have toast or potatoes, shrimp grits had 4 pieces of shrimp in it, french toast extremely dry (no butter or syrup was plated with it). Mimosas were almost all orange juice and she didn't come by nearly enough for refills (the glasses were those tiny tasters you use for New Year's toasting). We really wanted to like this place because the inside is beautiful and I think the hate they got leading up to their opening about the $60 gold chicken wings was unfair. They really need to focus on training their staff and rounding out the rest of the menu beyond the buffet. You can't rely on a $30 brunch buffet and not have any coffee in stock when there's so many other brunch places in the neighborhood
The Ambiance is nice. Clean and neat establishment. Try the Tempura Cauliflower; it's delicious!
Had brunch today with my friends , the  atmosphere  Was Great the staff was excellent especially Courtney and most of all food was  fantastic . I  definitely will be going back.
The drinks and service was exceptional!! Kimmie was the best bartender. She was attentive and made a drink that was beyond what I expected. I love the civil and I will be back soon.
Great service with good food and live band amazing ✨❤️
Great service, awesome food with a touch of class!!!
Food is delicious!

Wow this place was very unorganized. The server was nice but needed some more training. She sat down while taking our order, our food was extremely late and not good to me at all. I probably won't be trying this place again.

The experience here was very distasteful. The restaurant used excuses as to why they were out of crab and steak. In Baltimore, Maryland that’s unacceptable. Most of the menu consists of items where crab and steak were add ons that would have made the meal even better. The drinks were good though. Waiters were very sweet as well.
Good but not great food. Nice brunch buffet. Generous servings. Tasty drinks. Pretty atmosphere.  Excellent service. No coffee served, which is vexing when at brunch.

Very nice spot!
Service was great.Didn't wait long for food and drinks. Restaurant very clean atmosphere and music was delightful.
Just starting out but wasn't impressed with the food Looked better than it tasted
